UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest ->
GetPrivilegedApiControl; update=GetWorkRequest
-> GetPrivilegedApiControl;
delete=GetWorkRequest ->
GetPrivilegedApiControl/ListPrivilegedApiControls
confirm-delete
supported drift: approverGroupIdList,
definedTags, description, displayName (+6 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId
create-only fields: none
list lookup:
oci_apiaccesscontrol_privileged_api_controls
filters compartmentId, displayName,
resourceType, id; Adopt only a unique exact
ListPrivilegedApiControls match on compartmentId
plus displayName plus resourceType in ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING; duplicate matches fail,
and pre-create lookup is skipped when any of
those identity fields are empty.
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Create, update, and delete persist the in-flight
OCI work request in `status.async.current`,
normalize API Access Control `OperationStatus*`
values into shared async classes, and normalize
work-request `OperationType*` values into
create/update/delete phases before deriving
conditions and requeue behavior.
Create prefers the returned
`PrivilegedApiControl` body when OCI exposes an
identifier and otherwise recovers the OCID from
work-request resources before polling
`GetPrivilegedApiControl`. Update also gates
completion on a succeeded work request plus a
readable `GetPrivilegedApiControl`.
Only `displayName`, `description`,
`notificationTopicId`, `approverGroupIdList`,
`resourceType`, `resources`,
`privilegedOperationList`, `numberOfApprovers`,
`freeformTags`, and `definedTags` reconcile in
place. `compartmentId` remains replacement-only
drift, so the published runtime never exercises
provider-only
`ChangePrivilegedApiControlCompartment`.
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats `FAILED` and
`NEEDS_ATTENTION` as terminal failure without
requeue, and delete retains the finalizer until
`GetPrivilegedApiControl` or fallback
`ListPrivilegedApiControls` confirms the
resource is deleted or not found.
end note
